The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to catch on fire, resulting in injuries or fatalities. It can also lead to unexpected acceleration, loss of power, and loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: especially in the ignition switch or alternator area; the engine accelerates unexpectedly; the vehicle shuts off without warning; the engine continues to run after the ignition is turned off; the seatbelt warning system fails to work; the warning lights and sounds go off simultaneously; the vehicle experiences a loss of power and control.
